26;s:25:"Turn it off and on again.";i:27;s:23:"Test the Doors Balance.";i:28;s:99:"Perhaps the greatest cause of a garage door that will not open all the way up is a lack of balance.";i:29;s:70:"Test your doors balance by disconnecting it from the automatic opener.";i:30;s:47:"The door should raise and lower easily by hand.";i:31;s:48:"Pull your garage door so its about halfway open.";i:32;s:28:"Do not stand under the door.";i:33;s:45:"Do not attempt this if the door is wide open.";i:34;s:55:"It will come crashing down and could cause some damage.";i:35;s:78:"This is best for when the door wont open or if it close to the ground anyways.";i:36;s:89:"If the door still does not budge the problem may be with the tracks rollers or springers.";i:37;s:95:"Lift your garage door to its farthest extent and clamp vise grips on the tracks to jam it open.";i:38;s:106:"If you have an automatic garage door opener unplug it and disconnect it from the door using the pull cord.";i:39;s:88:"If your opener is not plugged into an electrical socket it may be wired into a subpanel.";i:40;s:96:"To manually open most garage doors you simply pull a corded handle that is attached to the door.";i:41;s:88:"This disengages the electric drive from the door and you can manually open and close it.";i:42;s:64:"To reset it begin by pulling the cord in the opposite direction.";i:43;s:25:"It should click in place.";i:44;s:65:"Once this happens you can open and close the door electronically.";i:45;s:97:"Not being able to open and close your garage door with a remote can be an annoying inconvenience.";i:46;s:115:"If you cant close your garage door with the remote specifically meant for it there could be various issues at play.";i:47;s:125:"There are some fixes you can make to the door yourself as well as a few things you can do to use your garage in the meantime.";i:48;s:157:"If your garage door isnt closing and is backtracking its way up to the open position the sensors being bumped out of place could be the cause of the problem.";i:49;s:53:"You can resolve this problem by leveling the sensors.";i:50;s:47:"Most modern sensors have a red indicator light.";i:51;s:93:"- If neither handset opens the garage door then try to re -code the handsets to the operator.";i:52;s:149:"- If only one of the remote handsets does not work then try replacing batteries and if this does not work then purchase a replacement remote handset.";i:53;s:39:"If you have power and you can hear the.";i:54;s:97:"Hi all I bought the IRIS garage door opener and installed it on my Craftsman Garage Door Openers.";i:55;s:72:"The install went fine I have the leads connected and paired with my hub.";i:56;s:53:"However 50 of the time the garage door does not open.";i:57;s:154:"When I click OpenClose depending on state the ZWave unit will beep and flash so I know its getting the signal however after the 5 seconds nothing happens.";}}